headline.main: Airstrikes Alone May Not Defeat Sunni Militants
headline.print_headline: Airstrikes Alone May Not Defeat Sunni Militants

docs.lead_paragraph: In their Syrian strongholds, extremists from the Islamic State group had been moving into civilian apartment buildings for cover days before the U.S. and its allies began pounding them before dawn Tuesday, activists say. It's just one sign of the difficulties in trying to destroy the group by relying mainly on airstrikes.
